FBIS3-13488 "drnes050dd_94005" FBIS-NES-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Pledges Revolution `Until Victory' LD1403181394 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403181394 Algiers Voice of Palestine Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Yesterday morning brother President Abu 'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] visited the martyrs' cemetery in Tunis accompanied by members of the Palestinian leadership and revolutionary cadres. After the brother president and those attending had recited Surah al-Fatihah [opening verses of the Koran] for the souls of the innocent martyrs, brother President Abu 'Ammar gave an address in which he stressed that the waterfall of Palestinian blood would not halt for one moment until the Palestinian flag and the flag of the Arab nation were raised over the walls, minarets, and churches of Jerusalem. Brother President Abu 'Ammar made a pledge to all the martyrs that the revolution, on whose long and difficult road they had fallen, would continue, however great and long the sacrifices and however much the difficulties increased, through the determination and will of our people until victory and as far as Jerusalem.
